  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Gayatri Balasamy versus M/s ISG Novasoft Technologies Limited pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_4_2080_2236','2025INSC605'); ><font size='4'> <strong>GAYATRI BALASAMY<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>M/S ISG NOVASOFT TECHNOLOGIES LIMITED </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2080</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 605</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005602025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJIV KHANNA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, BHUSHAN RAMKRISHNA GAVAI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SANJAY KUMAR, AUGUSTINE GEORGE MASIH, K.V. VISWANATHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration In &Dagger;M. Hakeem and Anr.&rsquo;s case, this Court held that while exercising powers u/s.34 of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996, a Court hearing the petition had no power to &ldquo;modify&rdquo; the Award, of two judges and three judges of this Court have either modified or accepted modification of the arbitral awards. In view of the divergent and contrasting judicial opinions as regards the power of the court u/s.34 to modify an arbitral award, the matter has been placed before the Constitution<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 30-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6178/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 5 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclic